---
import Layout from 'layouts/LayoutLanding.astro';
---

<Layout title="Chinese Visa – GOSIM Hangzhou 2025" description="Information about the venue for GOSIM Hangzhou 2025">
  <section
    class="section speaker-detail-header"
    data-theme-section="light"
    data-bg-section="light"
  >
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Chinese Visa</h1>
      <br><br>
      Most attendees are now eligible for visa-free entry or transit, some may still need a visa depending on their nationality and travel plans.
      <br>
      Please read the updated requirements below, and contact your local Chinese embassy or consulate for precise instructions.
      <br><br><br>

      <h2>Visa-Free Entry (up to 30 days)</h2>
      <br>
      Citizens from 74 countries, including most EU nations, Australia, New Zealand, and several Latin American countries, can now enter China visa-free for up to 30 days.
      <br>
      This applies to tourism, business, visiting family/friends, or short conferences.
      <br>
      These policies are valid at least until December 31, 2025 for many countries.
      <br>
      Always confirm eligibility with your local Chinese consulate.
      <br><br>
      Examples of <a style="color: #0089328b; font-weight: bold;">VALID</a>  transits:
      <ul>
          <li>Japan -> China -> Japan</li>
          <li>Singapore -> China -> Singapore</li>
      </ul>
      <br>
            Examples of <a style="color: #ec0000; font-weight: bold;">INVALID</a>  transits:
      <ul>
          <li>USA -> China -> USA</li>
          <li>UK -> China -> UK</li>
      </ul>
      
      <img src="/images/subpages/visa-exemption.png" alt="Visa Exemption Map" style="max-width: 800px; width: 100%;">
       Image credit: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visa_policy_of_mainland_China#Visa_exemption" style="color: #007BFF; text-decoration: underline;" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a>
      <br><br><br>

      <h2>Visa-Free Transit (up to 10 days / 240 hours)</h2>
      <br>
      Travelers from 55 countries including the US, Canada, UK, Japan, and many EU states may enter China without a visa if transiting through to a third country.
      <br>
      This policy allows stays of up to 240 hours in designated regions — including Hangzhou.
      <br>
      You must have confirmed onward travel and meet entry requirements.
      <br><br>
      Examples of <a style="color: #0089328b; font-weight: bold;">VALID</a>  transits:
      <ul>
          <li>USA -> China -> Japan</li>
          <li>UK -> China -> USA</li>
      </ul>
      <br>
      Examples of <a style="color: #ec0000; font-weight: bold;">INVALID</a>  transits:
      <ul>
          <li>USA -> China -> USA</li>
          <li>UK -> China -> UK (round trip)</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/subpages/visa-free-transit.png" alt="Visa Free Transit Map" style="max-width: 800px; width: 100%;">
      Image credit: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visa_policy_of_mainland_China#Visa_exemption" style="color: #007BFF; text-decoration: underline;" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a>
     
      <br><br><br>

      <h2>Traditional Visa Applications</h2>
      <br>
      If you are not eligible for visa-free entry or transit, or plan to stay longer, you will need to apply for a Chinese visa.
      <br>
      Most attendees will apply for a Tourist (L) or Business (F) visa.
      <br>
      You will need:
      <br>
      – A passport valid for at least 6 months with at least 2 blank pages
      <br>
      – A completed visa application form with a recent passport photo
      <br>
      – A round-trip flight booking and hotel reservation, or a GOSIM invitation letter
      <br><br>

      <strong>Invitation Letter</strong>
      <br><br>
      After completing your registration and ticket payment, GOSIM can provide an invitation letter to support your visa application.
      <br>
      Please <a href="mailto:travel@gosim.org" style="color: #007BFF; text-decoration: underline;">email us</a> with your passport name, nationality, and registration confirmation if needed.
      <br>
      Allow sufficient time — visa processing may take 7–10 business days or longer.
      <br><br>

      <strong>Useful Links</strong>
      <br><br>
      – China Visa Info & Appointment: <a href="https://www.visaforchina.cn" target="_blank">visaforchina.cn</a>
      <br>
      – Country-specific entry policies: <a href="https://www.china-briefing.com/news/china-visa-free-travel-policies-complete-guide/" target="_blank">China Briefing – Visa-Free Guide</a>
      <br>
      – Chinese Embassy Listings: search for your local Chinese consulate or embassy online
      <br><br>

      We highly recommend checking the most up-to-date information via your country's embassy or consular website before traveling.
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

